# Files exempt from the "no upstream hosts" CI guard.
# gitignore-style path globs; one per line. See .github/actions/no-upstream-hosts/README.md
#
# Rule of thumb: only tooling that intentionally references the upstream host in
# order to REWRITE it, migration provenance, and human documentation belong here.
# Application/runtime code must never be allowlisted.

# The guard's own scanner contains the host pattern it searches for.
.github/actions/no-upstream-hosts/**

# Documentation legitimately names the upstream project (PenguinMod) and its hosts
# when explaining the migration and the runtime-independence success criterion.
**/*.md
**/*.mdx
src/content/**
